translation.text: Delays to some services due to lightning strikes damaging signalling equipment near Loftus earlier. Please allow additional travel time, listen for announcements and take extra care when boarding & alighting trains.

Buses replacing trains between Mt Victoria, Lithgow and Bathurst in both directions due to infrastructure damage caused by bushfires. 

There is no forecast when the line can reopen. Please allow additional travel time and check transport apps for further details.

due to lightning strikes damaging equipment at Valley Heights earlier. Buses may supplement some services. Train stopping patterns may change at short notice. Please listen for announcements, check transport apps or platform screens before boarding trains.

Big Bash League: Sydney Sixers v Hobart Hurricanes - Sydney Cricket Ground, Moore Park
From 19:00 until 22:10
- The closest station to the SCG is Central. Change for a light rail service to Moore Park leaving from Chalmers Street stop.
- Alternatively you can also walk to Moore Park via Devonshire Street and the Albert 'Tibby' Cotter Walkway.

Illawarra Folk Festival 2020 - Bulli Showgrounds, Bulli
From 17:00 until 23:00
- The closest station to the festival is Bulli on South Coast Line which is a short walk from the Showgrounds. 

Details: https://transportnsw.info/events/2020/01
Be weather wise and avoid rushing and stepping in puddles to prevent slips, trips and falls.

From Thursday 2 until Saturday 25 January, the Southern Tunnel at Central Station will be temporarily closed due to Sydney Metro works. To access platforms 4-23 please follow signs and use the Suburban Tunnel or the Northern Concourse. For more information about Sydney Metro works, visit sydneymetro.info

The public toilets at St James Station are closed while major works are taking place. Public toilets are located at the Elizabeth Street entrance to the right and in Hyde Park through the Macquarie Street tunnel up the stairs to the right. We apologise for any inconvenience.

New Metro Platforms are being constructed on platforms 1 & 2 at Sydenham Station. From 6 January 2020, T3 services to the City will operate from platform 3 & T3 services to Lidcombe and Liverpool will operate from platform 4. Platform 4, 5 & 6 upgrade works - A new Metro concourse is also being constructed at the Northern end of the station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5. If you need help, please see staff at the station. For more information on theseUpgrades, please see sydneymetro.info
